\xd5 s most Excellent Majesty, by and with the advice and
consent of the Lords Spiritual and Temporal, and Commons, in this present
Parliament assembled, and by the authority of the same, as follows:
Repeal of the European Communities Act 1972
The European Communities Act 1972 is repealed.
Secondary legislation made under that Act shall continue in force unless it is
subsequently amended or repealed, and any such amendments or repeals may
be made by statutory instrument subject to annulment in pursuance of a
resolution of either House of Parliament.
The Secretary of State may be order made by statutory instrument repeal any
Act which is rendered obsolete by virtue of the repeal in section
No order may be made under subsection

ParaLine.String: unless a draft of the order has been
laid before and approved by a resolution of each House of Parliament.
The Secretary of State must, within one month of this Act coming into force,
put in place measures to commence the withdrawal from or the denunciation
of the Treaties listed under section 1 of the European Communities Act 1972.
This Act may be cited as the European Union (Withdrawal) Act 2013.
This Act comes into force on such day as the Secretary of State may appoint by
This Act extends to England and Wales, Scotland and Northern Ireland.
